 <record>
       <attribute name="title">Funding</attribute>
       <attribute name="tag">funding</attribute>
       <attribute name="text">
       <![CDATA[
FungiDB is a member of pathogen-databases that are housed under 
the NIAID-funded <a href="http://www.eupathdb.org">EuPathDB</a> 
Bioinformatics Resource Center (BRC) umbrella. The EuPathDB team is 
mainly distributed between the University of Pennsylvania in 
Philadelphia, Pennsylvania and the University of Georgia in Athens, 
Georgia.

FungiDB was initially funded through a grant from the <a
href="http://bwfund.org/">Burroughs Wellcome Fund</a> to Jason Stajich
(UC Riverside) and David Roos (University of Pennsylvania and
EuPathDB). <br>

       ]]>
       </attribute>
   </record>



 <record>
       <attribute name="title">Data Access Policy</attribute>
       <attribute name="tag">use</attribute>
       <attribute name="text">
       <![CDATA[

The data at this site is provided freely for public use, through the
contributions of many researchers including those involved in
generating the genome sequences. The data is not guaranteed to be
accurate as it often reflects the results of ongoing research.  When
using data obtained from FungiDB or an EuPathDB project, it is
important to cite the original publications and contributors of that
data.

Please see Citing FungiDB below.

       ]]>
       </attribute>
   </record>


